A dermatome      is the area of skin supplied by the cutaneous sensory fibres contained within a single spinal nerve and therefore arising from a single spinal level.  
A myotome      is the group of muscle cells controlled by the somatic motor fibres contained within a single spinal nerve, and therefore arising from a single spinal level. These muscle cells may be distributed, during development, into several different muscles, and can therefore control one or more movements.
